{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013Y1LaY3mh5BTgnonBmRPZZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The rollback to 3.9 is also failing with the same feature flags error. This is strange - 3.9 should be the original version...\n\nWait, I think what happened is:\n1. When 3.12 started (briefly), it wrote feature flag state to the mnesia database on the PVC\n2. When we rolled back to 3.9, the 3.9 image reads the feature flag state file that 3.12 wrote\n3. 3.9 doesn't understand the `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag entry, OR more likely, the 3.12 upgrade wrote some data that 3.9 can't roll back from\n4. But the error message says \"required feature flag not enabled\" which is from 3.12, not 3.9 - so maybe the pod is still running the 3.12 image despite the rollback\n\nLooking at the rollout status, it says \"Waiting for 3 pods to be ready\" but only rabbitmq-0 is visible and it's in CrashLoopBackOff. I suspect the issue is with the `maxUnavailable: 3` setting - it might be preventing the rollback from completing properly. The rollback is changing the image back to 3.9, but with `maxUnavailable: 3` and OrderedReady policy, all three pods get deleted before any are recreated. Since rabbitmq-0 fails to start with 3.9, the other pods never get created. The 3.9 failure might be due to feature flag metadata that 3.12 wrote to the PVC, which 3.9 can't handle. The feature flags state file is stored in the mnesia database on the PVC, so I could mount it in a temporary pod and delete it to let 3.9 start fresh. But that risks causing other issues if the mnesia database was partially upgraded. I need to think through whether there's a safer approach to recover from this state.\n\nActually, the real issue is that we skipped enabling the `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag in 3.9 before upgrading to 3.12. The 3.12 node is now refusing to start because it requires that flag to be enabled first. We're already past the point where we can enable it in 3.9, so I need to either reset the mnesia data entirely or find a way to manually enable the feature flag in the PVC data. The feature flags state lives in the mnesia database at `/var/lib/rabbitmq/mnesia/<node>/feature_flags`, so I could mount the PVC in a separate pod using the 3.9 image to enable the flag before upgrading. Since the current pod is stuck in CrashLoopBackOff, the PVC isn't in use, so I should be able to attach it to another pod to modify the feature flags file directly. The issue might be that 3.12 wrote incompatible feature flag metadata to the mnesia directory during that brief startup, and now 3.9 can't parse it. Or the rollback didn't actually switch the image back to 3.9. I should verify what version is currently running in the StatefulSet.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1217,"cache_read_input_tokens":44180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1217},"output_tokens":16,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7477e209-d8ca-4ef9-8a94-60016f704d9e","uuid":"8c4b91df-ccda-48a1-8df7-cd237b469e8f","request_id":"req_011CcPzDan1pX4BCtQ9gNDjH"}
