{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015ncne783fdafSWjGUnnLCC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so:\n- The StatefulSet has `replicas: 1` (only rabbitmq-0 exists as a pod)\n- The `currentRevision` and `updateRevision` are the same (`rabbitmq-78fccc7df4`), which means the rollback has been applied but the update is stuck because rabbitmq-0 (3.12) is not becoming ready\n- All 3 PVCs still exist\n\nThe problem is: the rollback set the template to 3.9, but the StatefulSet controller needs to update pod-0 from 3.12 to 3.9. \n\nWith OrderedReady policy, the controller should first recreate the missing pods 1 and 2 (in ascending order) before attempting the rolling update, but since only pod-0 exists and isn't becoming ready, the controller might be blocked from proceeding with pod creation.\n\nThe real puzzle is that both currentRevision and updateRevision point to the same revision (rabbitmq-78fccc7df4), suggesting the controller thinks the update is complete, yet pod-0 is still running the old image (3.12) instead of the new one (3.9). This could mean the controller considers the rollback \"done\" because all existing pods match the target revision, even though they're not actually ready or properly updated.\n\nThe StatefulSet controller needs to replace pod-0 with a fresh instance running 3.9, but with OrderedReady semantics, it won't proceed until the missing pods 1 and 2 are created and ready first—creating a deadlock where nothing can progress. The rolling update direction goes from highest to lowest ordinal, so the controller would update pod-2 first, then pod-1, then pod-0. But since pod-2 and pod-1 don't exist, the OrderedReady policy creates a catch-22 where they can't be created until pod-0 is ready. A simpler solution might be to scale the StatefulSet down to zero to delete all pods, then scale it back up to three with the correct image version.\n\nWhen scaling back up, pod-0 starts first and forms its own cluster, then pod-1 joins when it discovers pod-0, followed by pod-2. The existing PVC data from the 3.9 version should remain intact, so the cluster should reform correctly as each pod comes online and reads its data from storage.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3792,"cache_read_input_tokens":48625,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3792},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7477e209-d8ca-4ef9-8a94-60016f704d9e","uuid":"a32400c0-099e-4f5a-82be-6c004cdf2a56","request_id":"req_011CcPzMewGfQtwXQryGVxC8"}
