{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0172DekR9Df6BWAzTga2aDXE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Upgrade complete. Here's the summary:\n\n**All goals achieved:**\n- All 3 nodes running **RabbitMQ 4.1.8** (4.1 family) on Erlang 27.3.4.13\n- Cluster is healthy with all 3 nodes running and not under maintenance\n- `/app` vhost exists\n- `app-queue` exists with **5 messages preserved** and in `running` state\n\n**What happened and why:**\n\nThe upgrade path was `3.9 → 3.11 → 3.12 → 3.13 → 4.0 → 4.1` — not a direct 3.9→3.12 jump. RabbitMQ 3.12 requires the `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag to be enabled before upgrade, but that flag was only introduced in 3.10. So the necessary intermediate step at **3.11** was to enable all feature flags (including `classic_mirrored_queue_version`) before proceeding.\n\nA recovery detour was required: the first attempt to jump 3.9→3.12 directly caused a CrashLoopBackOff, and the StatefulSet entered an OrderedReady deadlock (pod-0 waited for Mnesia quorum, pods-1/2 waited for pod-0 to be Ready first). Breaking it required `rabbitmqctl force_boot` on the running-but-not-ready pod-0 to designate it as the cluster leader on next restart."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1403,"cache_read_input_tokens":74893,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1403},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7477e209-d8ca-4ef9-8a94-60016f704d9e","uuid":"d6f2a0cc-254f-4464-bfcc-6777dfad8b37","request_id":"req_011CcQ1rg1SAEdtNqNo7pBvq"}
